''Wanted: Monty Mole'' reached number 2 in the all-formats sales charts behind ''[[Daley Thompson's Decathlon]]''
<ref name='pcncharts22sep'>{{cite magazine |title=Charts|magazine=Personal Computer News|issue=|publisher=VNU|date=22 September 1984|page=5|url=https://archive.org/details/PersonalComputerNews/PersonalComputerNews079-22Sep1984/page/n5/mode/2up|access-date=6 December 2022}}</ref> in the week up to 13 September 1984. It topped the ZX Spectrum charts in the same week<ref name='pcncharts22sep' /> before being replaced by ''Daley Thompson's Decathlon'' the following week.<ref name='pcncharts29sep'>{{cite magazine |title=Charts|magazine=Personal Computer News|issue=|publisher=VNU|date=29 September 1984|page=4|url=https://archive.org/details/PersonalComputerNews/PersonalComputerNews080-29Sep1984/page/n5/mode/2up|access-date=6 December 2022}}</ref> Gremlin Graphics reported that they had sold 20,000 copies in the first six weeks.<ref name='pcg12charts'>{{cite magazine |title=Top 50|magazine=Personal Computer Games|issue=12|publisher=VNU|date=November 1984|page=21|url=https://archive.org/details/Personal_Computer_Games_Issue12/page/n19/mode/2up|access-date=6 December 2022}}</ref>

The game received a positive reception from critics. ''[[Crash (magazine)|Crash]]'' rated it 92%, describing it as a "fantastic ''[[Jet Set Willy]]'' type of game with excellent graphics and a good use of colour throughout".<ref>{{cite magazine | url=https://spectrumcomputing.co.uk/page.php?issue_id=976&page=8 | magazine=Crash | publisher=Newsfield | title= Wanted: Monty Mole | issue=9 | date=1984-09-27}}</ref> ''[[Personal Computer Games]]'' gave it 80%, saying "if you can put up with a measure of frustration, Monty Mole will unearth a great deal of action for your money", while also praising the graphics.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://archive.org/stream/personalcomputergames-magazine-11/PersonalComputerGames_11#page/n47/mode/1up | title=Personal Computer Games Magazine Issue 11}}</ref>

It also won ''[[Crash (magazine)|Crash]]'' magazine's readers award for best platform game in 1984.<ref name=crashaward>{{cite magazine|title =Crash Readers Awards 1984 |date =January 1985 |url =https://archive.org/details/crash-magazine-12/page/n93/mode/2up |magazine =[[Crash (magazine)|Crash]] |publisher =Newsfield|issue =12 |pages =94–95|issn=0954-8661}}</ref>

==Sequels==
* ''[[Monty Is Innocent]]'' (1985). In this game, Monty has been sentenced to five years in Scudmore Prison for stealing a bucket of coal. Monty's best friend, the mysterious masked weasel, Sam Stoat, is determined to set Monty free.
* ''[[Monty on the Run]]'' (1985). In this episode, Monty is on the run from the authorities after his intervention in the Miners' strike. He must escape from his house and head for the [[English Channel]] and freedom in Europe.
* ''[[Auf Wiedersehen Monty]]'' (1987). In this instalment, Monty travels around Europe collecting money in order to buy a Greek island - Montos, where he can safely retire.
* ''[[Moley Christmas]]'' (1987). Released as a covertape with ''[[Your Sinclair]]'' magazine, Monty is tasked with recovering the [[source code]] to his latest game and getting it to the duplication plant.<ref>{{cite magazine|title =Moley Christmas |date =January 1988 |url =https://archive.org/details/your-sinclair-25/page/n15/mode/2up |magazine =[[Your Sinclair]] |publisher =Dennis Publishing |issue =25 |page =17 |issn=0269-6983}}</ref>
* ''[[Impossamole]]'' (1990), remaking Monty as a cape-clad superhero who is recruited by aliens to retrieve their sacred scrolls.
* ''Monty: Revenge of the Mole'' (2013), released after it was selected as the winner of a ''Monty Mole'' game design competition held by Games Britannia in British schools; the game was developed by Steel Minions Studio, as adapted from the winning design. All proceeds from sales of the games went to the charity [[SpecialEffect]], a charity aimed at helping physically disabled people play video games.<ref name=revenge>{{cite press release |date=February 7, 2013 |title=School-developed Monty Mole Game Released for launch of Games Britannia 2013 |url=https://www.gamasutra.com/view/pressreleases/186215/Schooldeveloped_Monty_Mole_Game_Released_for_launch_of_GamesBritannia_2013.php |url-status=live |publisher=Games Britannia |agency=Games Press, [[Gamasutra]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210110051709/https://www.gamasutra.com/view/pressreleases/186215/Schooldeveloped_Monty_Mole_Game_Released_for_launch_of_GamesBritannia_2013.php |archive-date=January 10, 2021}}</ref>

